@startuml sebs_benchmark_to_metrics_flow.puml
title SeBS Benchmark to System and Metrics Return Flow

actor Researcher
participant "SeBS Runner\n(run_*_bench.sh)" as Runner
participant "SeBS Benchmark Client\n(http_latency_bench.py / Cloudburst client)" as BenchClient
participant "System Under Test\n(Baseline | Boki | Cloudburst/Anna)" as SUT
participant "Runtime Event Emitter\n(forked repo instrumentation)" as Emitter
participant "Run Directory\n(results/raw/<run_id>)" as RunDir
participant "Collector\n(collect_http_run.py / collect_cloudburst_results.py)" as Collector
participant "Event Aggregator\n(event_metrics.py)" as EventAgg
participant "Normalizer\n(*_to_common_schema.py)" as Normalizer
database "Common Schema Outputs\nJSONL + CSV" as CommonOut

Researcher -> Runner: Start benchmark run
Runner -> Runner: Generate RUN_ID and RUN_DIR\nWrite metadata.json
Runner -> BenchClient: Invoke benchmark workload
BenchClient -> SUT: Send benchmark requests
SUT --> BenchClient: Return responses
BenchClient -> RunDir: Write latency/timing artifacts

SUT -> Emitter: Emit runtime events/telemetry (optional)
Emitter -> RunDir: Write events.jsonl / telemetry.json / extra_metrics.json

Runner -> Collector: Build collected_metrics.json from run dir
Collector -> EventAgg: Parse and derive event-based metrics (if events exist)
EventAgg --> Collector: reliability/disaggregation/CRDT-derived metrics
Collector -> RunDir: Write collected_metrics.json

Researcher -> Normalizer: Normalize collected metrics
Normalizer -> RunDir: Load collected_metrics.json (+ strict event checks)
Normalizer -> CommonOut: Write normalized JSONL/CSV

CommonOut --> Researcher: Cross-system comparable metrics
@enduml
